<h2>General responsibilities</h2>
<p>Operators are responsible for planning operations, maintaining aircraft in a safe condition, understanding local restrictions and ensuring pilots are competent for the intended activity.</p>
<h2>Safe operation principles</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Assess weather, terrain, bystanders and nearby aviation activity before launch.</li>
  <li>Maintain visual line of sight unless separately approved.</li>
  <li>Avoid unsafe proximity to people, vehicles, structures and emergency scenes.</li>
  <li>Respect privacy and data protection obligations under Endonian law.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Registration and approval overview</h2>
<p>Most operators will be expected to maintain a valid operator record once online services go live. Complex activity may require an operational authorisation based on risk and mitigations.</p>
<div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Do community groups need to follow these rules?</button><div class="faq-content" hidden><p>Yes. Community and hobby operators must still fly safely, remain within relevant operating limits and follow local restrictions.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Can a business fly over public events?</button><div class="faq-content" hidden><p>Public event operations are generally higher risk and likely to require a specific authorisation and detailed safety case.</p></div></div>
